011 included three SIAs, using a combination of monovalent oral poliovirus vaccine (mOPV) type 1 and bivalent oral poliovirus vaccine (bOPV) conducted within 7 weeks of notification of the case (the first SIA was held 7 days after detection), followed by monthly SIAs using bOPV for 6 months.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":621,"renderedHeight":539,"naturalWidth":621,"naturalHeight":539,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 558 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":31572},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/figures/m6043a3f3.gif","alt":"The figure shows wild poliovirus (WPV) cases (N = 43), by type in India and selected states during 2010 and 2011. During 2010, a total of 42 WPV cases (18 WPV1 and 24 WPV3) were reported in India in 17 districts in seven states.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":622,"renderedHeight":369,"naturalWidth":622,"naturalHeight":369,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":40874},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_pdf.gif","alt":"Adobe PDF file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":6058},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_word.gif","alt":"Microsoft Word file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":1087},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/